MINDFUL of the hunger and cold poor homeless people suffer in winter s freezing and rainy weather, a local community organisation collected trolley-loads of clothing, tin-foods, blankets and non-perishable items to donate to Cape Town s nine Haven Night Shelters. &nbsp; Rondebosch-based Peninsula 77 Round Table Winter Knights organisation hosted their annual one day street collection drive at Montclare Place in Claremont on Saturday. The organisation s public relations officer Thomas du Plooy said: It s now mid-winter and with the snow and cold fronts heading for Cape Town, it s difficult for the homeless and those who don t have shelter. We are passionate to help and uplift those who are desperately in need of clothing, food and blankets at this time of year.&quot; For more see the Cape Times on Monday. [email&#160;protected]